---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Ross Taylor is a New Zealand cricketer, born on 8th March 1984 in Lower Hutt, Wellington.
Taylor is a right-handed middle order batsman and bowls occasional right-arm offbreak.
Ross Taylor holds the record of having the most number of centuries scored by a New Zealander.
Ross Taylor captained the New Zealand U19 team during his youth international days.
He made his debut for state side Central Districts in the 2002-03 season.
